gale 🐸 lingli 10-Dec-21 07:12 PM
CURRENT TIME: 6:00 A.M. LOCATION: CAMP OFFICE_
Winter means the days are short. Late is dark in the morning, and early is dark in the evenings. You arrive at the camp office for your next case, early enough to beat the sun peeking behind trees. Footprints imprint the snow, creating a makeshift trail of slush. Hopefully you’ve gotten a good night’s rest. The same can’t be said for everyone in your band. Cold air blasts into the room every time the door swings open. Once it settles, so does the blanket of warmth that follows. Coffee and hot chocolate has already been prepared for those that want it. A blond man sits on the table, chatting leisurely with a red-head standing beside him. ;The red-head is judging his companion for being a lazy ass.

HOLD FOR ONE MOMENT
Two branches. Both stubbornly refusing to break. Sturdy through necessity, bent and warped to support a weight unasked for. But a burden shared is a burden halved. What shape might they take now? Come one. Come all. Come together.
From foreign grafts sprout [ “a new life” ].
Fragments stitch together. You know the meaning of sacrifice. The things you had to give up, the path you had to take to survive - to protect you and yours. But the pieces fit differently now. Your mother, [fit enough to lift a couch] stands healthily in your memories, [a joke always on hand] to bring matching smiles to your faces. Your father, gone - but the loss isn’t as devastating with more to fill the space left behind. What are siblings for, after all? Where life is rough, there is still joy to be found - in laughter, in a shoulder to lean on. The future comes easier, with less uncertainty. This is [ Your Family ]. Small but strong, tightly woven and most importantly- -You are not alone in this - the desperation from having no one to turn to vanishes. You are no longer just the protector, but the protected. +The broken pieces are no longer just yours to bear.
